In this code, I've replaced the cylindrical raindrops with flat planes that use the leaf image as a texture. Each droplet now has a width of `0.2` and a height of `0.4`, and they are falling at various speeds.

To implement the feature of waiting for the image to load before generating the raindrops, you'll need to create a preloader for the image. Below is the updated HTML code that incorporates this functionality while using the specified image (from Picsum) as raindrops.

```html
